name: DEAMONOLOGIE
description: In 1590 King James VI of Scotland,   later                                                  James I of England, became convinced that he and Queen Anne, his Danish wife, had been the target of witchcraft when witches called up fierce storms in order to kill the royal couple during crossings of the North Sea. James held onto this belief and shortly after becoming monarch of both England and Scotland in 1603 he published 'Daemonologie'
